40|$|The <b>issue</b> <b>of</b> <b>bonus</b> in life {{insurance}} is considered {{in a model}} framework where the traditional set-up is extended by letting the experience basis (mortality, interest, etc.) be stochastic. A novel definition of the technical surplus on an insurance contract is proposed, and basic principles for its repayment as bonus are discussed. Making the experience basis an endogenous part of the model opens possibilities of model-based prognostication <b>of</b> future <b>bonuses.</b> Numerical illustrations are provided. Safety margins, prospective reserves, retrospective reserves, stochastic interest, stochastic mortality, counting processes...|$|R
